Radisson Blu Hotel & Residence Nairobi Arboretum on Thursday held a grand opening in Nairobi. The guests were treated to an amazing evening filled with good music and great company. The luxurious hotel is a blend of nature and the city, providing a safe space to behold its beauty. Among the invited guests were Kepsa chairman Nick Nesbitt, Tourism CAS Joseph Ole Lenku andÂ Kenya Tourism Board CEO Betty Radie.